// @test regression/INV064-deep-namespace-no-false-positive
// @description The generalized deep-namespace member-call check must stay silent on VALID multi-level builtin calls (chart.point.new, strategy.risk.max_drawdown) and on user-defined-type constructors/methods reached through a chain (the namespace PATH `Foo.bar` is not a catalog prefix, so it is left alone). Guards the INV064 widening against false positives. See investigations/INV064-deep-namespace-member-calls/notes.md.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects no-errors
//@version=6
strategy("x")
p = chart.point.new(time, bar_index, close)
strategy.risk.max_drawdown(50, strategy.percent_of_equity)
plot(p.price)
